題目： Given a list of string, if length of strings is longer than x, print those strings<br />
input: ['abcd','abcde','abc'], 3<br />
output: ['abcd','abcde']<br />
我用正常if else solve到, 咁x一定要係int，諗緊用try except得唔得，有冇可能一入int以外嘅x即刻error<br />
<pre><code data-type="">def long_string(list, x):
    new_list=[]
    if isinstance(x, int):
        for i in list:
            if len(i)&gt;x:
                new_list.append(i)
    try:
        return (new_list)
    except TypeError:
        return ('x must be an integer')</code></pre><br />
發現就算入int以外嘅x，咁只係觸發唔到condition，並唔係error，所以最後return new_list即係 []<br />
有冇可能用try except解決到?<img src="/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif" class="hkgmoji" /><img src="/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif" class="hkgmoji" />

咁仲有個麻煩d既方法<br />
就係整個勁長list<br />
再用list index<br />
因為index淨係收integer<br />
收float就會value error<br />
<pre><code data-type="">    lst = [1,2,3,4,5,6,7,8,9]
    try:
        lst.index(x)
    except ValueError:
        return ('x must be an integer')</code></pre><br />
但點解唔可以try晒成段<img src="/assets/faces/normal/wonder2.gif" class="hkgmoji" /><br />
<br />
<pre><code data-type="">def long_string(list, x):
    new_list=[]
    try:
        if isinstance(x, int):
            for i in list:
                if len(i)&gt;x:  
                    new_list.append(i)
        else:
            raise TypeError('x must be an integer')
        return (new_list)
    except TypeError:
        return ('x must be an integer')</code></pre>

